      • getNamedSubInstance

        public static org.eclipse.uml2.uml.InstanceSpecification getNamedSubInstance(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.InstanceSpecification owningInstance,
                                                                             String name)
        Find a sub instance via its name. This is in particular useful for connectors that cannot be found via a slot, since UML only supports structural features (a connector is only a feature) in the definingFeature attribute of a slot.
        Parameters:
        owningInstance - an owning instance
        name - name of the sub-element (unqualified)
        Returns:
        the found sub-instance or null

      • chooseImplementation

        public static org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Class chooseImplementation(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Class componentType,
                                                              org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.InstanceSpecification> nodes,
                                                              ImplementationChooser chooser)
        Automatically choose an implementation, i.e. if the passed classifier (1) is already an implementation, simply return it (2) is an implementation group, choose the first implementation that fits the requirements (3) is a type: choose the first implementation among the heirs that fits the requirements
        Parameters:
        componentType - a component type or implementation (class, optionally abstract)
        nodes - a set of instance specification representing nodes on which this component will be allocated
        chooser - A chooser for an implementation in case of multiple candidates
        Returns:
        a suitable implementation
